VCDM (aka CDMI-proxy)
---------------------

VCDM is an implementation of CDMI-compatible server that can be used to store data both using local infrastructure
and public cloud services.

Implementation supports:
- Blobs
- MQ
- Multi-level containers (also for single-level backends, e.g. AWS or Azure)

=== SETUP ===
1) Get the contents of the repository.
	- git clone git://github.com/livenson/vcdm.git

2) Get dependencies:
	- install required Python packages (most of them could be installed through easy_install):
		- Zope.Interface: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/zope.interface
		- Twisted: http://twistedmatrix.com
		- CouchDB-Python: http://code.google.com/p/couchdb-python/			
		- py-amqplib: http://barryp.org/software/py-amqplib/
	- install RabbitMQ: http://www.rabbitmq.com/
	- install CouchDB: http://couchdb.apache.org/  (at least version 1) 

If you are using Ubuntu:
	- apt-get install python-zope.interface python-twisted python-boto python-amqplib rabbitmq-server
	- Ubuntus come with a too old couchdb/python-couchdb. To fix that:
		- get couchdb from ubuntuone repo:
			- sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ubuntuone/stable
			- sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install couchdb 
		- sudo easy_install CouchDB  (to get python-couchdb)
		
There are several backends available at the moment. If you are planning to use them, you also need to get the
corresponding libraries (and put them on the PYTHONPATH or into $vcdm/libsrc:
	- AWS: http://code.google.com/p/boto/	
	- CDMI: https://github.com/livenson/libcdmi-python
	- Azure: https://github.com/livenson/winazurestorage
	
3) Copy vcdm.conf.template to vcdm.conf.

4) Run start-server.sh/start-server.bat.
	- by default, ports 8080-8081 will be accessible.
	- 8080: debugging access - no encryption or authZ
	- 8081: production access - encryption and authZ


